  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "2ONpF/OT/SI+yNr8jX8+4jR7OlU=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:39.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Document operations in Powerhouse follow specific naming conventions:\n\n- **Operation names**: `VERB_NOUN` or `VERB_NOUN_SUBJECT` in SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `ADD_TODO_ITEM`, `UPDATE_USER_PROFILE`)\n- **Input types**: PascalCase with `Input` suffix (e.g., `AddTodoItemInput`)\n- **Reducer functions**: camelCase with `Operation` suffix (e.g., `addTodoItemOperation`)\n\nWhen adding operations in Vetra Studio, you only provide the operation name (e.g., `ADD_TODO_ITEM`) and the `Input` suffix is generated automatically.\n\nOperations are organized into **modules** (e.g., a `todos` module containing ADD_TODO_ITEM, UPDATE_TODO_ITEM, DELETE_TODO_ITEM). This modular organization helps manage complexity as document models grow.\n\nDesign principles for operations:\n- Should be granular enough to represent distinct user intentions\n- Input types should contain all necessary info and nothing more\n- Use optional fields for partial updates (e.g., `text: String` without `!` in UpdateTodoItemInput)",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:39.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:39.000Z"
    }
  },
